    markdown:

      ElephantDatabase.org is the online home of the African Elephant Database,
      maintained by the [IUCN SSC African Elephant Specialist Group (AfESG)](http://www.iucn.org/african_elephant).

      ElephantDatabase.org presents data from past [African Elephant Status Reports](report/Loxodonta_africana),
      as well as more recent survey data reported to the specialist group. Data on this web site is made available under a
      [Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlikeÂ license](http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0).

      ElephantDatabase.org is an Open Source software project.  Every aspect of 
      the database is powered by free and open source software.  We are especially 
      thankful for [PostgreSQL](http://www.postgresql.org"),
      [PostGIS](http://postgis.refractions.net), and the open source tools that 
      make them possible.  We also would like to thank 
      [Google Fusion Tables](http://google.com/fusiontables) for serving up
      simple and free visualizations of our geospatial data.

      Request Data
      ----------------

      To obtain direct data access to African elephant data, please review our
        [data access and release policy](/about/darp) and
        complete the [data request form](/data_request_forms/new) online.

